<h2 class="alignLeft">What are EMF<span>s</span>?</h2>

<p>EMF stands for electromagnetic field, a form of radiation created by the movement of electrical charges. Although they’re not visible, EMFs exist everywhere around us. Natural sources like the sun and thunderstorms create EMFs, and so do the many devices in our daily lives.</p>

<p>Our daily exposure to EMFs is rising with our use of technology. Electricity, cell phone signals, Wi-Fi, and Bluetooth all contribute to an environment that can add stress on our bodies and lives.</p></cms cms1>
